<br>
The real advantage of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is you can reclaim injured pets for full mana.  If you adapt your tactics to take advantage of this, it can be incredibly powerful.<br>
<br>
Just one example of how to use this skill.  A group with multiple mages.  At any given time, usually one pet is taking most or all the beat down.  A mage with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reclaims the injured pet for full mana before it dies, and recasts it.<br>
<br>
A group of such mages can sustain chaining pets into an enemy forever while gaining, not losing, mana.  If they were non-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mages, then they would just be letting the pets die, and would consume more mana.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> involves changing the way you use reclaim energy.  I thank cousin <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Jochan</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for pointing out the utility of this ability.<br>
